      <acqinfo id="aspace_0f766cbc68ae376d5701e695d80ca14f">
         <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
         <p>The Nineteenth-Century Photography Collection was housed in the former Drama Library until its transfer to the Robert B. Haas Family Arts Library in 2008.</p>  
      </acqinfo>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_c43c217f39034bce83fa23b4c9c4835a">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The materials are open for research.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
      <userestrict id="aspace_a9e19e284ded2c012363570ee0847627">
         <head>Conditions Governing Use</head>
         <p>Copyright has not been transferred to Yale University.</p>  
      </userestrict>
      <prefercite id="aspace_3d0d1be33d9d72d5ab794b1ac80ec441">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Nineteenth-Century Photograph Collection, Robert B. Haas Family Arts Library, Yale University.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_56cab0e58d8edc0140a367c04cb7ff6e">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The collection consists of nineteenth-century photographs and carte de visite. Many images depict stage personalities from the United States and Europe in costume.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_e06881f5829c92d74bd741efe3d24c75">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>Arranged alphabetically by title.</p>
         <p>Please note that the alphabetical arrangement is letter by letter. For example, some materials have been ordered according to the initial article "The" and others by the designation "Handwritten," to indicate an inscribed caption. A portion of the collection is unidentified and undated. The entire box listing should be consulted in order to determine holdings.</p>  
      </arrangement>
